WEBVTT

00:00.610 --> 00:02.752
What an incredible, incredible blessing.

00:02.872 --> 00:03.093
Wow.

00:03.753 --> 00:04.494
You may be seated.

00:04.514 --> 00:06.016
I'm so honored to be here.

00:06.136 --> 00:16.547
It makes it so easy when you come to people whose lives actually are the epitome of certain things that we would have.

00:16.927 --> 00:24.195
I think that Pastor Dave and Pastor Kim, they are just the epitome of humility.

00:26.697 --> 00:27.218
Really.

00:29.346 --> 00:41.120
I think, you know, if you know how you have certain people that are just multi-gifted and multi-talented, if you looked almost, I think, in Heaven's dictionary for humility, I think that you would find their picture.

00:43.022 --> 00:44.284
And also excellence.

00:45.285 --> 00:46.987
They don't do things in a shabby way.

00:47.047 --> 00:48.549
They are people of excellence.

00:49.009 --> 00:53.575
Thank you for the excellence that you model, for the glory of the kingdom of God.

00:53.615 --> 00:56.338
Thank you for modeling generosity.

00:57.090 --> 01:02.938
Wow, in such an incredible way, they are generous, generous people and what an incredible blessing.

01:02.958 --> 01:03.198
Wow.

01:03.959 --> 01:05.301
And it takes a gift.

01:05.361 --> 01:08.805
I mean, I know some people that can't even stay together for 42 weeks.

01:11.769 --> 01:13.892
This is not anything to sneeze at.

01:13.972 --> 01:15.935
This is something to be celebrated.

01:15.955 --> 01:20.761
The goodness of God, and we've seen the growth of God, the blessings of God.

01:21.642 --> 01:24.626
This is proof positive that this thing works.

01:25.378 --> 01:26.500
No, it really, really is.

01:26.580 --> 01:27.621
And so I'm so grateful.

01:27.641 --> 01:28.402
I'm so grateful.

01:28.422 --> 01:29.403
I'm so grateful.

01:30.044 --> 01:35.191
But I want to talk to you today from the book of Psalm, chapter 71.

01:35.211 --> 01:39.878
It's a Psalm of David and verse 15 through verse 21.

01:40.839 --> 01:50.693
You'll notice that these words that all day long, David says, I will tell you the wonderful things that you do to save your people.

01:52.134 --> 01:54.738
But you have done much more than I could

01:54.850 --> 02:01.739
possibly know, I will praise you Lord God for your mighty deeds and your power to save.

02:02.580 --> 02:10.031
You have taught me since I was a child and I never stop telling about your marvelous deeds.

02:10.952 --> 02:13.936
Don't leave me when I'm old and my hair turns gray.

02:14.977 --> 02:20.044
Let me tell future generations about your mighty power.

02:21.066 --> 02:24.370
Your deeds of kindness are known in the heavens

02:24.610 --> 02:25.691
No one is like you.

02:27.033 --> 02:34.982
You made me suffer a lot, but you will bring me back from this deep pit and give me new life.

02:36.024 --> 02:41.851
You will make me truly great and take my sorrow away.

02:41.931 --> 02:44.694
Hallelujah to the Lamb of God.

02:46.496 --> 02:52.043
And I'm speaking today simply from the subject, what legacy are you leaving?

02:52.403 --> 02:54.546
What legacy are you

02:54.658 --> 02:55.219
leaving.

02:56.160 --> 03:01.707
This is really about King David, and he didn't just have an easy life.

03:01.727 --> 03:05.812
I want you to realize life has its ups and downs.

03:06.333 --> 03:10.819
Have you ever been to a hospital room and seen a person hooked up to all kinds of machines?

03:11.740 --> 03:16.986
And one of the things that you see is this thing, beep, beep, beep.

03:17.687 --> 03:22.994
Life is a collection of both hills and valleys.

03:23.234 --> 03:26.538
and heals and valleys, and heals and valleys.

03:26.738 --> 03:34.607
I know you would love for everything to just be chill and calm all the time, but you really don't want to be flat-lined.

03:36.870 --> 03:46.982
It is a sign that you are alive and that God is with you when he's with you, when you feel on top of the mountain, and some days when you feel like you're down in the valley.

03:47.803 --> 03:50.226
David said that he had been in both places.

03:50.562 --> 03:59.232
But I tell you this, if you are in the valley, that's not the time to quit, because what follows a valley is another mountain.

04:00.394 --> 04:08.544
You can't go from mountaintop to mountaintop, the shortest distance to get to the next mountain is down through the valley.

04:09.505 --> 04:14.771
It's the waters that's up on the mountain that flows down in the valley that makes the ground so fertile.

04:15.312 --> 04:20.338
You see, the mountains give us perspectives, but the valleys mature us.

04:20.674 --> 04:24.278
And I don't know about you, but I wouldn't take anything from my valley experiences.

04:24.919 --> 04:27.882
Your valley experiences are the thing that makes you who you are.

04:27.922 --> 04:33.368
It's the thing that actually will prove whether or not your relationship with God is true or not.

04:34.048 --> 04:36.211
It's not that he's just God of the mountain.

04:36.251 --> 04:38.934
He's God just as much when you're in the valley.

04:39.514 --> 04:46.642
God was just as much a God for David while he was tending sheep as he was when he was sitting on the throne.

04:47.010 --> 04:52.376
But just rest assured that if you feel like you're in a valley experience, just hold on because another mountain awaits you.

04:53.277 --> 04:55.280
You do know that God is for you, don't you?

04:56.061 --> 04:58.023
I just believe it with all of my heart.

04:58.563 --> 05:03.309
But it's the question that I'm asking to you today is what legacy are you leaving?

05:04.691 --> 05:14.482
Thirty-plus years ago, thirty-four years ago, actually, I started putting billboards, maybe twelve, fifteen billboards, big billboards around the city of Atlanta.

05:15.746 --> 05:18.970
And I asked this question on the billboard, what legacy are you leaving?

05:20.432 --> 05:22.235
What legacy are you leaving?

05:23.296 --> 05:24.258
Now, I'm a young man.

05:24.278 --> 05:28.804
I was in my 20s when I started doing this, in my 20s.

05:30.106 --> 05:40.820
But the reason that I started asking about what legacy are you leaving is because my daddy at that time was about 70.

05:42.523 --> 05:44.946
And you got to start where you are.

05:45.570 --> 05:57.483
And it's, I wanted to start thinking about where I was going, you know, and the thing is this, is that whenever you start somewhere, you have to ask this question, how do I want to be remembered?

05:58.724 --> 06:00.326
How do I want to be remembered?

06:00.626 --> 06:01.707
And I want you to think about this.

06:02.688 --> 06:05.311
Legacy is more than just about you.

06:06.572 --> 06:11.858
Legacy at its deep core is about his story

06:12.674 --> 06:15.879
being expressed down through your story.

06:17.021 --> 06:30.603
How do you use whatever you have gone through in your life to point to the fact that Jesus is Lord and victorious and is glorious and that he is healer and lawyer?

06:30.623 --> 06:33.688
Dr., I meant that he's a comforter.

06:33.728 --> 06:40.178
We wanna be able to express his story through our story.

06:40.322 --> 06:41.243
It's about him.

06:41.383 --> 06:42.664
It's really not about us.

06:43.685 --> 06:49.851
I mean, if you've met somebody of great notoriety, wouldn't it be silly for you to just be talking about your name?

06:51.473 --> 06:56.838
When the one that you really are excited about, you know, is it got a bigger reputation than yours?

06:58.319 --> 07:09.490
I mean, I mean, suppose some of you that that of my generation, you know, I grew up in the Michael Jackson generation, you know, if I went out and had dinner with Michael Jackson, you know, I wouldn't be talking about what I did.

07:11.266 --> 07:12.468
I want to talk about what he said.

07:12.508 --> 07:18.216
If I had dinner with Elvis Presley, I wouldn't be talking about what I was, I'd tell you what he ate.

07:19.858 --> 07:25.125
And I would tell you the content of his story, what we chatted about.

07:25.285 --> 07:26.387
I would talk about that.

07:26.467 --> 07:34.478
And so when you're talking about, it's actually his story that is expressed through our story.

07:34.498 --> 07:36.942
What legacy are you leaving?

07:37.142 --> 07:38.023
I'm in my wife or not.

07:38.043 --> 07:40.146
We were invited by,

07:40.226 --> 07:44.731
Julio Iglesias over to Italy and then to Israel.

07:45.632 --> 07:46.733
We had dinner with him.

07:47.754 --> 07:57.223
Now, it didn't matter of anything about who we were and what we did because we would, with somebody who was known around the world, this man was like a superstar.

07:58.605 --> 08:02.509
And we were sitting at dinner with him and my wife asked him, she said, how did you get into singing?

08:03.670 --> 08:07.634
I had never heard this part of his testimony before, but he said to us this, he said,

08:08.866 --> 08:10.588
He said, I was a champion soccer player.

08:10.608 --> 08:12.932
That's all that I ever dreamed of being and doing.

08:12.972 --> 08:20.583
And he said, I sustained a very deadly injury that left him paralyzed from the waist down for two years.

08:22.145 --> 08:26.631
While he's on his hospital bed trying to recuperate, somebody brings a guitar to him.

08:26.671 --> 08:33.761
And they said, well, while you're here trying to recuperate, you may as well do something with your time and teach yourself how to play this thing.

08:33.801 --> 08:37.106
And there he started working

08:37.378 --> 08:37.959
and doing it.

08:37.999 --> 08:42.907
And then they came back to see him and all of a sudden he had mastered the guitar.

08:43.608 --> 08:47.074
And then they said to him, these words, well, you ought to try to sing something.

08:48.136 --> 08:49.178
And the rest is history.

08:50.801 --> 08:52.503
And he sings in seven different languages.

08:53.645 --> 09:01.218
And so you see, our experience that had nothing to do with me is about his story that was expressed through our story.

09:01.939 --> 09:03.602
And as we live this earth,

09:04.034 --> 09:07.137
I know you have hard times and God has rescued us.

09:07.217 --> 09:19.750
I mean, we've got testimonies of how He saved us and car accidents, how He's raised us from sickness and on all of these things, how He's helped us with our children when we thought we were gonna kill them.

09:19.770 --> 09:29.320
And God has been faithful, but it's really not so much about us, it's about His story.

09:29.861 --> 09:31.122
Our legacy

09:31.266 --> 09:33.790
is how do we preserve history?

09:34.231 --> 09:36.214
David was saying, God, don't let me die.

09:36.254 --> 09:43.065
Don't let me get grayheaded and die before I'm able to show your power to another generation.

09:43.986 --> 09:45.269
Let me tell them about you.

09:45.389 --> 09:46.470
It's not about me.

09:47.011 --> 09:53.682
Even though I'm king, but don't let me die without telling them about you.

09:55.138 --> 09:58.542
We ought to be able to live our lives in such a way that I were grandchildren.

09:58.562 --> 10:03.068
My wife and I have 18 grandchildren and two more on the way that I be here before the end of this year.

10:05.471 --> 10:06.553
This is bigger than us.

10:06.853 --> 10:15.665
Our legacy is sometimes that you've got to be able to plant a seed that will grow a tree under which you may never sit under its shade.

10:15.705 --> 10:18.468
That's legacy.

10:19.049 --> 10:22.994
It is being able to say, Lord, I'm going to be a part of something that outlives me.

10:23.714 --> 10:25.336
Legacy is not about the past.

10:25.797 --> 10:28.380
Legacy is about everything that you said in motion.

10:28.400 --> 10:34.848
It blesses my heart to see the beauty of young people feel with music and energy and dance.

10:34.928 --> 10:47.002
Being able to express to me, it says that church on the rock will continue to live as a testimony of Jesus Christ from the faithfulness of a man and a woman that said yes to God.

10:47.984 --> 10:53.170
And that realize that even when they were having a hard time and struggling in the beginning years,

10:53.346 --> 10:59.434
they realized that God was for them in the same way that God is for you.

11:00.355 --> 11:01.056
What legacy?

11:01.076 --> 11:01.797
What legacy?

11:02.097 --> 11:03.939
What legacy are you leaving?

11:04.280 --> 11:05.341
Here's what legacy is.

11:05.441 --> 11:18.738
Legacy is the spiritual, moral, material and generational impact that a person leaves behind through their faithfulness to God.

11:19.106 --> 11:30.580
their obedience to His Word and the fruit of their life that continues to influence others after they're gone.

11:31.621 --> 11:35.245
It's just something there to remember and remind us.

11:35.626 --> 11:38.790
Legacy in Scripture is like a river.

11:39.150 --> 11:43.215
It is something that flows from one generation to the next.

11:44.236 --> 11:45.618
From generation it's like,

11:45.794 --> 11:58.089
Legado, it actually has to do with the flowing of a river that carries the memory of God's faithfulness and the imprint of a life that is well lived.

11:58.249 --> 11:59.350
It's like a river.

11:59.851 --> 12:03.075
It's something that flows out from you that keeps on going.

12:03.155 --> 12:03.916
But here's the deal.

12:05.137 --> 12:06.880
Legacy is not automatic.

12:07.921 --> 12:10.043
It is intentionally transmitted.

12:11.365 --> 12:15.570
You have to intentionally transmit legacy.

12:16.354 --> 12:18.536
Children just don't get things automatically.

12:19.397 --> 12:20.558
You have to be intentional.

12:21.459 --> 12:28.226
My God, what a gift this ministry is to you to be able to give you the Dave Ramsey program free for a year.

12:28.446 --> 12:29.207
What a gift.

12:29.507 --> 12:30.889
I hope that you realize the blessing of that.

12:31.069 --> 12:32.490
Let me just tell you this.

12:33.211 --> 12:37.435
My young man that I started mentoring, he was nine years old Mexican.

12:38.396 --> 12:40.318
And he ended up marrying my second daughter.

12:42.140 --> 12:44.242
And he had to pay for the Dave Ramsey program.

12:45.346 --> 12:47.849
He's my son-in-law now, and he works for me.

12:48.791 --> 12:52.836
And he and my daughter have a five-bedroom home.

12:53.657 --> 12:54.638
They're in their 30s.

12:55.860 --> 13:00.706
But his five-bedroom home is completely paid off, and I didn't give him a dime for it.

13:03.190 --> 13:05.453
He learned some things through the Dave Ramsey program.

13:05.813 --> 13:15.346
I hope you realize the gift that's been given to you, you ought to celebrate the generous heart of a leader that had the vision and the mindset to be able to say, listen,

13:15.522 --> 13:17.728
That's the equipment that's empowering you.

13:17.748 --> 13:19.613
It's endowing you.

13:19.633 --> 13:26.672
It's enabling you to be able to do some incredible things that I'm just here to just celebrate the goodness of God in your life so that you can realize it.

13:27.454 --> 13:30.642
And so legacy is not automatic.

13:30.754 --> 13:31.635
It's intentional.

13:32.036 --> 13:36.681
And this is how it started off with intentionality in Deuteronomy chapter six and verse seven.

13:37.061 --> 13:43.309
Notice, you know, God was telling Moses, he said, listen, you shall teach these things diligently to your children.

13:43.489 --> 13:46.773
Teach them diligently, intently to your children.

13:47.053 --> 13:57.746
And you shall talk of them when you sit in your house and when you walk by the way and when you lie down and when you rise up, because you know, children have a gift of ignoring you.

13:59.170 --> 14:02.257
And sometimes when you talk to your children, you don't know whether they're listening or not.

14:02.999 --> 14:09.293
And sometimes we are just pleasantly surprised to discover, you know what, that they were listening to me when I didn't even know that they were listening to me.

14:10.175 --> 14:17.010
And what an incredible blessing that that is because there are so many other things to distract them.

14:17.346 --> 14:28.798
with social media, with digital distractions that we have to have some intentionality where we shall teach them diligently to your children because somebody else is in their ears and before their eyes all the time.

14:29.059 --> 14:40.951
And so he said, that's why you ought to do it while you're sitting in your house, while you walk by the way, when you lie down, when you rise up, you ought to learn the blessing of the table to be able to get the family together and turn off the digital distractions.

14:41.632 --> 14:47.058
And sometimes, you know, I would say, you know, to my children, you know, listen, whoever picks up their telephone is going to pay the tab.

14:49.314 --> 15:06.980
that work like a charm to keep the phones in their place so that we can have an opportunity to be able to discuss the things of God and how God's blessings and what the meaning of the word of God has in our life and to say, what is God doing to you?

15:07.000 --> 15:09.504
What is God saying in your life and in your world?

15:09.524 --> 15:16.855
What a marvelous opportunity to be able to use the power of the table to be able to remind us of the goodness of God.

15:17.696 --> 15:18.898
You see,

15:18.978 --> 15:21.981
Legacy is not just a singular type of thing.

15:22.062 --> 15:25.986
Legacy, it's not just wealth, it's wealth and wisdom.

15:27.047 --> 15:29.590
You wouldn't want them to have wealth without any wisdom anyway.

15:31.072 --> 15:32.794
Legacy is wealth and wisdom.

15:33.314 --> 15:37.359
Legacy includes possessions, but it also includes principles.

15:38.300 --> 15:43.346
Because if you got stuff, if you got power, but no principles, you are a destructive force.

15:43.970 --> 15:51.349
It can be, it is more than just monuments, it's monuments and the multiplication of godly influence.

15:52.211 --> 15:54.437
It's monuments and multiplication.

15:54.718 --> 15:56.402
This building is a monument.

15:57.538 --> 16:04.708
But it's really, it's greatest power is the multiplication of Godly influence every time someone surrenders to the lordship of Jesus Christ.

16:05.189 --> 16:18.867
Every time somebody discovers their purpose on the inside of them to say that God wants me to be a businessman, a businesswoman, that God wants me to go into politics, that God, you see, I mean, these are calls of where you realize the purposes of God expressed out in the world.

16:19.568 --> 16:21.491
Legacy, legacy, hear me carefully.

16:21.852 --> 16:26.578
Legacy is where success and destiny meet

16:26.690 --> 16:27.611
but don't compete.

16:29.553 --> 16:35.400
Legacy, it is where success and destiny meet, but they don't compete.

16:36.501 --> 16:40.165
Legacy is remembered obedience.

16:40.826 --> 16:43.789
It is remembered obedience.

16:43.870 --> 16:46.773
Legacy is remembered obedience.

16:47.374 --> 16:47.794
You know what?

16:47.874 --> 16:54.802
It's remembered so beautifully in Hebrews 11 that we call the Hall of Fame of Faith.

16:55.042 --> 16:58.867
You know, it wasn't a remembrance of their disobedience.

16:58.887 --> 17:02.332
It was a remembrance of their obedience.

17:02.392 --> 17:04.816
Isn't it wonderful that God will remember your obedience?

17:05.236 --> 17:10.604
And I'm so glad that He didn't give us just a whole book listening all of their failures.

17:10.624 --> 17:16.412
But they had to come through something and they had to be challenged to where it cost them something.

17:16.472 --> 17:20.979
But legacy is about remembered obedience.

17:20.999 --> 17:23.442
It's about remembered obedience.

17:23.522 --> 17:25.906
By faith, Abraham did so and so.

17:26.387 --> 17:28.390
By faith, Sarah did this.

17:28.510 --> 17:30.914
By faith, the harlot did this.

17:31.415 --> 17:37.745
It's telling you as an act of their own faith, it's actually remembered obedience.

17:37.765 --> 17:46.820
So when somebody says, you know, I remember so and so, that becomes a legacy of your faith is your obedience that you did to God.

17:47.862 --> 17:50.386
And legacy is covenant continuity.

17:50.818 --> 17:52.580
It is covenant continuity.

17:53.000 --> 17:56.364
The way you've made a covenant with God, you are a covenant people.

17:57.145 --> 17:59.788
You come here because you're in covenant with God.

18:00.509 --> 18:02.551
You're in covenant to be able to worship Him.

18:02.611 --> 18:06.155
You're in covenant with your tithes and offering committed to Him.

18:06.516 --> 18:07.938
God is a God of covenant.

18:08.338 --> 18:10.801
The covenant doesn't just start with mama and dad.

18:10.941 --> 18:14.105
It goes down to the children and the grandchildren.

18:14.225 --> 18:15.967
It started before you.

18:16.968 --> 18:18.930
It's covenant continuity.

18:19.042 --> 18:27.711
You see Genesis chapter 17 and verse seven notice what he says, and I will establish my covenant between me and you.

18:28.152 --> 18:45.330
And I'm not going to leave your family out and your offspring after you throughout their generations for an everlasting covenant to be God to you and to your offspring after you.

18:45.538 --> 18:49.145
Make a covenant with God is the best way to ensure that God will take care of your children.

18:50.748 --> 18:56.518
They can look like they're wayward and away from God, but I'm telling you, God will send goodness and mercy after them.

18:58.181 --> 19:07.218
It may look like they're living for the devil, like they're living in rebellion against God, but listen, that's not how the story will end because God is a God of covenant.

19:07.426 --> 19:13.893
God will reach down and get your granddaughter and your grandson because he will remember the faithfulness of your prayers.

19:14.273 --> 19:20.760
Sometimes you're giving your sacrifice to God will say that because of that, I will remember your son and your daughter.

19:21.060 --> 19:25.264
I will redeem them from the hand of the enemy and I will use them for the glory of God.

19:28.407 --> 19:34.834
Godly legacy is when you live in such a way that others love God more because you lived.

19:36.258 --> 19:37.520
That's a godly legacy.

19:38.301 --> 19:44.570
It's when others are able to love God more because you lived.

19:45.271 --> 19:49.438
They're able to love God more just because you live.

19:49.558 --> 19:52.442
So you build something that helps others to stand taller.

19:53.143 --> 19:55.967
You have to realize that your legacy is about passing on faith.

19:56.047 --> 19:57.810
It's about passing on character.

19:58.190 --> 20:00.314
It's about passing on values.

20:00.334 --> 20:01.996
It's about passing on truth.

20:02.637 --> 20:06.002
You let your life become a bridge

20:06.210 --> 20:11.177
through which others can then walk into their promised land.

20:12.279 --> 20:21.412
Your life ought to be a bridge where the continuity of the life and the bridge is also the thing that connects them to generational blessings.

20:22.413 --> 20:31.546
So even if nobody was able to do things positively in your family until now, thank God that you are the one that will shift the destiny of your family.

20:33.089 --> 20:34.130
Because sometimes

20:34.530 --> 20:38.254
You might be the first one in your family who was able to keep that marriage together.

20:39.234 --> 20:43.719
Because sometimes divorce is a spirit that will attack a family and run rampant through the family.

20:44.019 --> 20:49.684
And maybe, maybe if you'll be faithful to God, God will say that if you'll do this, I will break the spirit of divorce in your family.

20:50.145 --> 20:52.147
I will break alcoholism in your family.

20:52.487 --> 20:54.469
I will break drug addiction in your family.

20:54.829 --> 20:57.271
I will break starting and stopping in your family.

20:57.652 --> 21:04.338
I'll give them the ability to be able to be diligent and to put their hand to the plow and not look back, but be faithful unto God.

21:04.450 --> 21:06.032
God will honor your family.

21:06.052 --> 21:07.895
I'm just telling you, all he needs is a bridge.

21:08.636 --> 21:18.090
Just a connector that if you know God and if they don't know God, all you have to do is just touch them and then touch God and power will flow through you.

21:22.977 --> 21:26.762
Inheritance is what you leave behind, but legacy is who you leave it with.

21:28.905 --> 21:32.370
It's left to your children and your grandchildren and your great-grandchildren.

21:33.218 --> 21:36.642
Let me give you a little acronym for legacy, legacy.

21:36.662 --> 21:38.765
Let's look at it on a cross stick here.

21:39.085 --> 21:42.349
